UNITED STATES, Appellee, v. George Frederick GUNDELFINGER, Appellant. No. 7713. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. May 21, 1941. H. F. Stambaugh, of Pittsburgh, Pa., for appellant. George Mashank, of Pittsburgh, Pa. (Charles F. Uhl, U. S. Atty., of Pittsburgh, Pa., on the brief), lor appellee.

Before BIGGS, MARIS, and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the district court is affirmed.
